// EXPECT: did you mean 'Green'
// "Did you mean?" spelling suggestion: an unknown variant close to a real one
// (Levenshtein within threshold) suggests the nearest name. All real variants are
// present here, so the ONLY error is the typo'd `Gren` — with its suggestion.
en Color { Red, Green, Blue }
fn pick(c:Color) -> i64 {
  mt c {
    Red => 1;
    Gren => 2;
    Green => 3;
    Blue => 4;
  }
}
println(pick(Red))
